  <module>neptune</module>
  <modulesummary>neptune command</modulesummary>
  <description>
    <p>neptune is a tool for creating a skeleton erlang application or release
    using GNU Autotools as the build system.</p>
  </description>
  <section>
    <marker id="command_line"></marker>
    <title>Using neptune</title>
    <p>neptune can be used to create a skeleton erlang application or
    release. The resulting structure of files can be built, tested and
    installed.</p>
    <p><em>Exit status:</em></p>
    <taglist>
      <tag><c>0</c></tag>
      <item>
        <p>Processed successfully.</p>
      </item>
      <tag><c>1</c></tag>
      <item>
        <p>An error occurred</p>
      </item>
    </taglist>
    <code type="none">neptune [--version]</code>
    <p><em>Options:</em></p>
    <taglist>
      <tag><c>--version</c></tag>
      <item>
        <p>Print the neptune version and exit.</p>
      </item>
    </taglist>
  </section>
